{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"deac88b2-6574-42bd-84d2-b4d1b72e8327","content":"Here's how to migrate from `VSTest@3` to Microsoft.Testing.Platform while keeping TRX reports and code coverage:\n\n### 1. Update your test project\n\nAdd to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### 2. Replace the pipeline task\n\nReplace `VSTest@3` with `DotNetCoreCLI@2` (or a plain `dotnet test` script):\n\n**Before:**\n```yaml\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testSelector: 'testAssemblies'\n    testAssemblyVer2: '**\\*Tests.dll'\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n```\n\n**After:**\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=TestResults.trx\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish test results'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish code coverage'\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n### Key differences\n\n| Concern | VSTest@3 | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|---|\n| Runner | vstest.console.exe | Built into the test binary via `dotnet test` |\n| TRX reports | Automatic | `--logger trx` flag |\n| Code coverage | `codeCoverageEnabled` | `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` |\n| Publishing | Handled by task | Separate `PublishTestResults@2` / `PublishCodeCoverageResults@2` steps |\n\n> **Tip:** Add `condition: always()` to the publish steps so results are uploaded even when tests fail.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1c724975-ec80-4a24-a963-92ef31335186","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory appears to be empty. The user is asking a general question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure DevOps pipelines. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":637,"requestId":"3408:9F564:58F6088:6108E5F:69F3FAD5"},"id":"fce52430-2fca-496c-bd70-c4ca1b30e433","timestamp":"2026-05-01T00:59:12.360Z","parentId":"797f751d-ffa5-4670-9ebb-114d7391f711"}
